<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06120152 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06120152 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  Seventy Sri Lanka government soldiers have died in three days of fiercefighting with Tamil Tiger rebels -- including 40 killed today when guerrillasambushed two army platoons comprising 50 soldiers, military officials said.Six soldiers were seriously wounded in the attack near Nanathan village in thenorthwestern Mannar district.;    Tamils, who make up 18 per cent of SriLanka's 16 million people, have long accused the Sinhalese of discrimination.The Sinhalese make up 75 per cent of the population.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  TAMIL REBELS KILL 70 IN SRI LANKA BATTLES  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  The World ... Briefly  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Stock Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910429  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Monday  </DAY><MONTH>  April  </MONTH><PG.COL>  7A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  83  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Monday April 29, 199100120152,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>